      p
        |Pseudo-classes provide access to an element's state. Illustrated best with links and the
        code :hover :visited :active
        |states.

      p
        |Pseudo-elements, on the other hand, provide access to an elements sub-parts, which can include portions of text nodes, for example with
        code ::first-line ::first-letter
        |.

      p
        |The major advantage of pseudo-classes and pseudo-elements is that they provide ways to hook-up styles without having to add classes without clear symantic value to the markup. Also, if changes are made such as adding more elements to the HTML, additional class names don't need to be added in order for the styling to take effect as desired. The first type considered is 
